On 14 Jan 99, at 8:00, Jake Frederick wrote:

> What's an easy way to stop the GameB command from checking the joypad
> buttons until they've been released? I'm trying to eliminate the autofir=
e
> thing so the player has to hit the button every time they want to fire
> instead of just holding it down. -- -If the doors of perception were
> cleansed everything would appear to man as it truly is, infinite.-

 That won't work, as the hardware in a joypad will make it appear as if th=
e 
person using it is pressing and releasing it, only very quickly. The only =
ways 
round this (I'll be happy to be proven wrong) are to decrease your program=
's 
sensitivty to fire being pressed, to a more humanly capable speed i.e. onl=
y 
accept fire button presses every 3rd frame or something.


