Well if you eventually DO develope a 100% safe anti-piracy software you h=
ave to keep it to yourself, and 100% secret, or someone will find out, an=
d break it. It's that simple. Also, you have to make the system so compli=
cated that nobody will have the time to bother cracking it, since it's mu=
ch easier to just buy the game.

I remember System 3 had a revolutionary (at the time) copy protection alg=
orythm. It took almost  years to develope, and 15 minutes to crack. (Prin=
ted at the bottom of the inside cover of the manual for Last NInja 2: Thi=
s game cannot be cracked, so don't waste your time." In fifteen minutes, =
it was not only cracked, it was also transfered to disc aswell.)

Also, you might want to look into the CDCop encryption scheme. It SHOULD =
work (as it is a combination of hardware/software protection). It will at=
 least detere some of the less professional thieves out there.


