Hi,

Just a thought...if you are programming the copper using os screens...then
you should build a user copperlist using the library commands (graphics or
intuition...I can`t remember...it`s been a long while since I did this) and
attaching it to a screens viewport. The only problem do that is it requires
the screen to be remade, and then the display to be remade, so that would
rule out using it for fancy constantly changing colour effects, but it is
the only 100% safe way to mess with a screens copperlist. And you really
shouldn`t be programming aga chips directly anyway, as it`s not very safe,
and not very future proof.

Dave




