@NODE "Mail_225" "Re: Reading CD ROM ID Numbers"
From: Rick Hodger <rick.thehub@bigfoot.com>
Date: Sun, 03 Jan 1999 13:27:46 +0000
Organization: Corrupted Software
Subject: Re: Reading CD ROM ID Numbers
Encoding: quoted-printable

I watched as Mikkel L=F8kke hammered "Re: Reading CD ROM ID Numbers" out
on their keyboard...

> Are you sure ? A friend of mine has a CD player that recogninses
something it calls a CD Serial number. Which does that use AMiGA or PC
?

Couldn't say.  You'd have ask the author of the program, there is no
set standard for recognising a CD.  It's left completely up to the
author of the program.

There is practically unlimited ways of recognising a CD in a CD-ROM
drive, plus there are so many shareware programs with their own ways
of doing it, even if you could introduce a standard people wouldn't
bother because they'd have to provide a converter to convert their own
format to the standard.

I have two CDPlayers on my miggy, between them they use about 4-5
different methods of storing CD info, CDID, OptyDatabase, CDDB and
CDDB/CDID hybrid.

-- =

