@NODE "Mail_248" "Re: Piracy"
From: "Matt Briggs" <s9225796@rothervalley.ac.uk>
Subject: Re: Piracy
Date: Wed, 13 Jan 1999 13:26:04 -0000
	charset="iso-8859-1"
Encoding: 8bit

Hello everyone!

I find that the best way to protect your exe programs against piracy
(especially when keyfiles and registration codes are involved) is to use a
packer program (such as PowerPacker) to pack up the exe file, which itself
encrypts the program. Then use a hex editor to screw up the PowerPacker file
header - and hey presto you can't unpack the program, yet you can still run
the file. You see?

Keep this info top secret! Don't let anyone know I told you!

Regards,
Matt Briggs


