I've seen something like it, the idea was o have a special dye on the
surface of the disc, then after being read in a CD-ROM, the dye turns
a nasty colour and prevents the disc from being read again.  Not a
very good idea where you may have to install a piece of software
several times...could get costly for the producer of the CD if he has
to keep sending people new copies every time their machine crashs and
they have to reinstall.

