I think I have the same problem once in a while. It`s usually best to
close down Blitz and restart again (the old Windows trick!) The problem
happens when you load some source from one location and SuperTED changes
the current directory for you. Then later you may load something else
in from elsewhere and the directory is changed again, when you`re
working
for a few hours and you`re loading/switching from various documents from
various locations eventually blitz decides to give you some kind of
weird file requestion that doesn`t let you choose anything! I must say
I don`t have any explanation or real solution but I`m glad to see I`m
not the only one to have this problem. Close down and restart is the
only
solution!

