@NODE "Mail_420" "Re: GTListview-read only?"
          Paris Sun, 31 Jan 1999 00:02:25 +0100 (MET)
From: Jean-Marc GIGANDET <HURRICAN@wanadoo.fr>
Date: Sun, 31 Jan 1999 00:02:34 +0200
Subject: Re: GTListview-read only?
Encoding: quoted-printable

Hello Curt

#GTLV_ReadOnly has nothing to do with that. It's #GTLV_ShowSelected which=
 will do the job.

If you want highlighted items, you can :
        1) attach a string gadget to it like that :

        GTString   #WindowNumber,#GTStrNumber , StrXPos,StrYPos,StrWidth,=
StrHeight,"String"  ,1,MaxLen
        *DefGad.Gadget=3DGTGadPtr(#WindowNumber,#GTStrNumber)
        GTTags #GTLV_ShowSelected,*DefGad
        GTListView #WindowNumber,#GTLVNumber, LVXPos,LVYPos,LVWidth,LVHei=
ght,"ListView",0,LVArray()


        2) if you don't have a string gadget attached, just give 0 when y=
ou define the GTTag, like this :

        GTTags #GTLV_ShowSelected,0
        GTListView #WindowNumber,#GTLVNumber, LVXPos,LVYPos,LVWidth,LVHei=
ght,"ListView",0,LVArray()


If you don't want highlighted items just forget the tag !

        =


Hope it'll help.
  =

Regards
