@NODE "Mail_434" "GFX card palettes"
From: Curt Esser <camge@ix.netcom.com>
Date: Tue, 19 Jan 1999 18:02:36 -0500
Subject: GFX card palettes

Hi Everybody,

I am attempting to convert a game to work on GFX cards, as well as standard
systems.  So, I have converted all graphics to be shown in a window (rather
than "ShowBitmap"), and all seems to be working fine on my standard AGA
system.

But now I see a discussion of LoadRGB32 - won't the standard palette
commands work on a GFX card?  Ie, loadpalette, use palette, etc...

If it matters, I am now using just the old ECS style colour commands,
although the game works fine on an AGA machine also.

Thanks...

                                    Yours electronically,
                                    Curt Esser
                                    camge@ix.netcom.com
                                    http://members.xoom.com/Curt_Esser/




@ENDNODE
