@NODE "Mail_481" "Re: Executing Programmes"
From: Curt Esser <camge@ix.netcom.com>
Date: Wed, 06 Jan 1999 19:49:22 -0500
Subject: Re: Executing Programmes

Hi James

On 06-Jan-99, James L Boyd wrote:

> 
> The numbers on the end are for mysterious stuff that nobody
> understands (or something) - just use 0,0 :
> 
> #Execute_# EXE$,0,0

This method will run the program, and your Blitz program will wait until it
ends.

If you want the Executed program to run on it's own, so your Blitz program
can continue, add "Run" to the command string, or "Run >NIL:" if
appropriate.

EXE$="Run YAM:YAM"
Execute_ EXE$,0,0

Will launch YAM and allow your program to continue.

Just think of Execute_ the same as if you were typing the command into a CLI
-
just about anything you can do in a CLI can be done as an Execute_ command,
including making Assigns, etc.  The only difference is that you must always
supply the COMPLETE path to the file.

                                    Yours electronically,
                                    Curt Esser
                                    camge@ix.netcom.com
                                    http://members.xoom.com/Curt_Esser/




