@NODE "Mail_484" "Re: Executing Programmes"
From: "Tony Rolfe" <edgewater@shoalhaven.net.au>
Organization: Edgewater Motel, Burrill Lake, NSW 2539 Australia
Date: 9 Jan 99 21:51:49 +1000
Subject: Re: Executing Programmes
Encoding: 7bit

On Sat, 09 Jan 1999 08:00:47 +0000 Rui Carvalho said:
> Hello James
> 
> Somewhere James L Boyd wrote:
> J
> JB > The numbers on the end are for mysterious stuff that nobody
> JB > understands (or something) - just use 0,0 :
Someone told me that they are for the input and output redirection
filehandles.  E.g. if you do a CLI command

Fred >file1 <file2

then you could do 

Execute_ (Fred,&filehandle1,&filehandle2)
Though why you would want to...

Cheers

-- 
Tony Rolfe
