@NODE "Mail_525" "Re: Debuggers!"
Date: Mon, 25 Jan 1999 05:17:59 -0800 (PST)
From: Thomas Cobb <thomcobb@yahoo.com>
Subject: Re: Debuggers!
  Blitz Mailing List <blitz-list@netsoc.ucd.ie>


> > I need Enforcer :) But I aint got an MMU :(((.. Well I have but only
> > an EC-MMU, and those dont work :(... Does Mungwall need an MMU?
> 
> Erm, EC processors don't have an MMU at all.  Mungwall is just a
clone of
> enforcer (or is enforcer a clone of Mungwall? I forget...)

All the chips are manufactured the same.  If the manufacturing process
fails and the MMU doesn;t work, but the rest of the chip is fine then
it is shipped as an EC version, so even the EC has an MMU, it just
doesn't work.  This is why it is so hard to detect if a MMU is
available, because it may say that a mmu is present but you don;t know
that it is working until you try a few instructions and your machine
dies a horrible death.

	Thom
