@NODE "Mail_552" "Re: Creating a game."
Date: Tue, 19 Jan 1999 04:08:45 -0800 (PST)
From: Thomas Cobb <thomcobb@yahoo.com>
Subject: Re: Creating a game.


---Oliver Marks <oly@enterprise.net> wrote:
 
> bullets what would be a good way of handling lots of bullets i have
> thought about using plot but that destroyes the back ground.


If you use shapes for the bullets then using buffers is quick and easy
Then you can use the BBlit and Unbuffer commands to draw them



> Can anyone give me an idea of how many shapes you can use on screen on
> a 256 colour bitmap before there is a noticable slow done.

