A Cookie: This is a bitmap, much like the actual shape, except instead of=
 holding the actual image data, it determines which points are plotted, a=
nd which aren't.

A Stencil: This is also a seperate bitmap except this time it defines whe=
re on the bitmap pixels can be plotted (so you can make a shape pass "und=
er" some of the bitmap graphics.)

