What a lode of twadale.  CDXL isn't in Ham.  CDXL (CDTV-A500) is 64/32
colours and is amazing for CPU power and CD-Rom access speed 150K/Sec.
Then there was update for CD32 which work with CD32 which was only
A1200, no 030 or fast mem.  For what was it was, it was dam good. 

But for modem A1200 it is a bit lame.  I am talking 030/50 or 040/25
or better.  But at the time they were not use that type of system. 
Carl did a very good job, just like he did with Exec.

And as point of order CDXL was first format that could be
double-buffered with Video and Audio.

-- 
