Hi Mikkel
Am 10-Jan-99 schrieb Mikkel L=F8kke:

> Hello.
> =

> How does the BltBitMapRastPort_ command from intuition work ?

It`s simple. Just create a bitmap with InitBitmap() or blitz command
Bitmap (you`ll need to peek the bitmap`s address then of coz)
create a rastport or open a window and use window`s Rastport
and then you can OS friendly and GFX card friendly blit a bitmap.
As minterm you should use $0C0 vanilla copy. I`m using BltBitmapRastport(=
)
whenever there`s some bitmap to blit (it works also fine with guigfx)

Keep `em coming!

> =

> Any examples aso. would be highly appreciated.
> =

> =

> Greets,
Regards
