>           DC.l  Address(String)
>           DC.b"Error"

> but I don't know the actual syntax.    Could it be done through a
> Macro?   Then I could simply say  !StrConst "Error".   =


Erm I think David Mcminn was closer :o) You could of course make you own =
string handling routines, or maybe use the ones in the New command set. M=
aybe it was time Frederic included things like Constant strings, and unsi=
gned byte, word and longword variable types. It's long overdue.


