From: "David Mcminn" <D.McMinn@eee.rgu.ac.uk>
Organization: The Robert Gordon University, E&EE
Date: Thu, 28 Jan 1999 17:00:21 -0000
encoding: Quoted-printable
Subject: Re: .q

> Does anyone know how a .q variable is stored?
> 
> Is it shifted left 16 places?

 Its a long word, the upper word (bits 31-16) are the integer part and the=
 
lower word (bits 15-0) are the fractional part. I think the whole thing is=
 one 
twos complement number rather than both words being a twos complement numb=
er.


